# Privacy Policy - DR-LAW

 

## Introduction

This Privacy Policy explains how DR-LAW ("we", "our", or "us") collects, uses, and protects user information in the DR-LAW mobile application.

DR-LAW is a Learning Management System (LMS) application designed to provide legal education and training courses. The platform enables users to access educational content, track their learning progress, and interact with course materials. By using this application, you agree to the terms of this Privacy Policy.

## Information Collection and Use

To provide and improve our educational services, DR-LAW collects necessary personal information when users create an account and use the platform.

### Information We Collect

When you create an account and use our services, we may collect:

- **Account Information**:
  - Full name
  - Email address
  - Phone number
  - Profile picture (optional)

- **Educational Data**:
  - Course enrollment information
  - Learning progress and completion status
  - Quiz and assessment results
  - Certificates earned
  - Course ratings and reviews

- **Usage Information**:
  - Course viewing history
  - Time spent on courses
  - Device information (model, OS version)
  - App version and crash logs

This information is used only for:

- Creating and managing your account
- Providing access to educational content and courses
- Tracking your learning progress and achievements
- Issuing certificates upon course completion
- Improving course content and user experience
- Communicating course updates and important notifications
- Providing customer support

### Information We Do NOT Collect

We do not collect sensitive personal data such as:

- Government IDs or passport information
- Financial or credit card information (payments are processed through secure third-party services)
- Precise location data
- Contacts from your device
- Media files unrelated to course activities

## Data Storage and Security

- User account and educational data are stored securely on our servers
- All data transmission is encrypted using industry-standard protocols (HTTPS/TLS)
- We implement appropriate technical and organizational measures to protect your information
- Access to user data is restricted to authorized personnel only
- We do not sell, rent, or share your personal data with third parties for marketing purposes

However, no method of electronic storage or data transmission is completely secure, and absolute security cannot be guaranteed.

## Subscription and Payments

DR-LAW may offer:

- Free courses and content
- Premium courses requiring payment
- Subscription plans for unlimited access

All payments are processed securely through:

- **Google Play Billing** (for Android)
- **Apple App Store** (for iOS)

We do not collect, process, or store any credit card or payment details directly. All payment information is handled by the respective platform's secure payment system.

## Third-Party Services

The app uses trusted third-party services to provide functionality:

- **Google Play Services** - for Android app functionality
- **Firebase** (if applicable) - for authentication and analytics
- **Payment Processors** - Google Play Billing / Apple Pay
- **Video Hosting Services** - for course video content delivery

These services may collect limited technical data necessary for app functionality, in accordance with their own privacy policies.

## Cookies and Tracking Technologies

DR-LAW may use cookies and similar tracking technologies to:

- Maintain your login session
- Remember your preferences
- Analyze app usage and performance
- Improve user experience

You can manage cookie preferences through your device settings, though disabling certain cookies may affect app functionality.

## Educational Content and Intellectual Property

- All course content, videos, materials, and assessments are the intellectual property of DR-LAW or licensed content providers
- Users are granted access to content for personal educational use only
- Unauthorized distribution, copying, or sharing of course content is prohibited

## User Rights

Under applicable data protection laws, you have the right to:

- **Access**: Request a copy of your personal data
- **Correction**: Update or correct inaccurate information
- **Deletion**: Request deletion of your account and associated data
- **Data Portability**: Request your data in a portable format
- **Withdraw Consent**: Opt-out of non-essential communications

To exercise these rights, please contact us using the information below.

### Account Deletion

Users may request account deletion at any time. Upon deletion:

- Your personal information will be permanently removed
- Your learning progress and certificates will be deleted
- Access to purchased courses will be revoked
- This action cannot be undone

## Data Retention

We retain your personal information for as long as:

- Your account is active
- Necessary to provide our services
- Required by law or for legitimate business purposes

Upon account deletion, we will remove your data within 30 days, except where retention is required by law.

## Children's Privacy

DR-LAW is intended for users aged 13 and above. We do not knowingly collect personal information from children under 13. If we become aware of such collection, we will take steps to delete the information immediately.

## Changes to This Privacy Policy

We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time to reflect changes in our practices or legal requirements. Any changes will be:

- Posted on this page
- Notified to users via email or in-app notification (for significant changes)
- Effective immediately upon posting

We encourage you to review this Privacy Policy periodically.

## Legal Compliance

We may disclose your information if required to:

- Comply with legal obligations or court orders
- Protect our rights, property, or safety
- Prevent fraud or security issues
- Enforce our Terms of Service

## International Data Transfers

Your information may be transferred to and processed in countries other than your country of residence. We ensure appropriate safeguards are in place to protect your data in accordance with this Privacy Policy.

